<h1>Meeting Tomorrow Provides Support to "Rally to Restore Sanity"</h1>
<strong>CHICAGO, IL &amp; WASHINGTON, DC - October 27, 2010</strong>Â - Meeting Tomorrow, a leading provider of nationwide audio visual services for corporate meetings and events, announced today that they are providing an in-kind donation of audio-visual services to assist in the Chicago satellite event of the Washington DC-based "Rally to Restore Sanity" led by Jon Stewart, on October 30, 2010.

"When approached by the event organizers, we gladly agreed to help support this event. As a company, Meeting Tomorrow remains independent and neutral in political matters," said Mark Aistrope, president of Meeting Tomorrow. "Like many others though, we are concerned that the discourse regarding issues important to our country has become overly-heated and often polarizing. We stand in strong support of any effort to help facilitate a different approach in Washington DC."

